Meta Title: 559 W Surf Street 800, Chicago, IL 60657 is now new to the market! - Urai Chiya
Meta Description: Rarely-available premier 8th floor unit in the historic Green Brier building constructed in 1901 in the heart of Lakeview. One-of-a-kind 3BR/2BA with stunning views in three directions. Just steps from Lincoln Park golf facilities, Lake Michigan, shopping, groceries, dining, gyms and transportation. Original oak flooring and trim in many rooms including a stunning oak and antico verde green marble fireplace. Feel at home every time you enter the grand foyer with massive original mirror and built-in oak bench. Large master bedroom suite with window-box seat windows looking out into western sunsets and Diversey and Clark intersection cafes. A walk-in closet and bright bathroom make these primary living quarters a cozy home in the sky. A social cook's dream kitchen with large granite island and stainless steel appliances overlooking the dining room and massive bay windows to an astonishing view down Broadway Street. Extraordinary views over an entire kilometer of the annual Chicago marathon course! Elegant and useful built-in bar cabinet and shelves. Plentiful storage cabinets. A jawdropping formal room boasts views towards fantastic architecture and historic streets, yet is high enough up for privacy. Mirrored display shelves, original oak mantle, and marble decorative fireplace. An original massive sliding pocket door makes this space perfect for hosting, home office needs, or music. A large second bedroom has sunset views to the west and a view immediately down the center of Broadway with its historic street lamps that has to be seen to be believed. A large closet provides ample storage. An elegant third bedroom or home office enjoys two massive windows with wood trim, and lovely views into the building courtyard and historic Surf-Pine Grove district architecture. Other features include an in-unit washer and dryer, central heat and air, thick masonry floors and walls that make the unit almost entirely soundproof, an assigned perfectly positioned indoor parking space in attached garage, staffed package room, passenger elevator, large service elevator, storage unit and handy bicycle storage space in the basement just off the building courtyard, as well as a storage closet in the apartment itself. The immediate neighborhood is one of the most livable in North America, with almost every cuisine represented, local tailors, dry cleaners, hardware, phone repair, antique store, cafes, gyms, and even an excellent cinema just around the corner. It doesn't get much better than this. Multiple grocery stores and shops await you within three blocks. Transit lines criss-cross the streets around the building, taking you uptown, downtown, to trains, to the airport, and beyond. All of these unique features come together to make an outstanding way to enjoy the best of Chicago.

Upstairs, discover a spacious game room and four additional bedrooms, each with its own full bath for ultimate convenience. Enjoy the outdoors on the covered porch and patio, and don't forget about the split 3-car garage – perfect for all your parking needs. Welcome home to the Sierra, where warmth and comfort await! Meta Title: 3401 Lee Parkway 1603 Dallas, TX 75219 MLS#20509197
Meta Description: 3401 Lee Parkway 1603 Dallas, TX 75219 $1,699,000 Beautifully updated Mayfair condo overlooking Turtle Creek and Arlington Hall with dazzling views of the Downtown Dallas skyline. Upon entering, you will be greeted by a spacious and versatile living and dining area. The kitchen has been thoughtfully updated with Calabasas countertops, a custom marble backsplash, breakfast bar with gas 5 burner cooktop, stainless Kitchen Aid microwave, dishwasher and electric convection oven. Two bedrooms with ensuite baths offer the opportunity to use one bedroom as a home office or media room. As a resident of the Mayfair, you will enjoy an array of amenities including The Sky Club and Mayfair Room for entertaining or a quiet place to savor the views. The third floor includes the garden terrace with lush landscaping, fire pit, pool, coffee bar and fitness center.

Meta Title: 3401 Lee Parkway 1503 Dallas, TX 75219 MLS#20488445
Meta Description: 3401 Lee Parkway 1503 Dallas, TX 75219 $1,399,000 Experience extraordinary living in this exquisite 2-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom luxury condo, with an office-flex room. This sophisticated residence boasts high-end finishes, a gourmet kitchen featuring top-of-the-line appliances, including a Brand New Built-In refrigerator, Built-In Miele Coffee Maker, and Built-In ice maker. The office-flex space is perfect space for your home office or another room to entertain guests, or even a potential nursery. Enjoy concierge services, an expanded meeting area, and immerse yourself in the peaceful vibe of this urban retreat. Enjoy views of Downtown Skyline, Arlington Hall, and Turtle Creek Park! Don't miss the chance to call this lavish condo your home!

Meta Title: 14918 Lake Forest Drive Addison, TX 75254 MLS#20468269
Meta Description: 14918 Lake Forest Drive Addison, TX 75254 $2,950,000 This 6467 Sq Ft home sits on a tree lined 1.1-acre lot within this exclusive neighborhood offering a seamless blend of luxury and convenience. This property is nestled by a creek and park, just moments from Dallas's best amenities, with quick access to the Tollway and 635. The exterior boasts timeless stone architecture and breathtaking drive up appeal while inside, the open floor plan features dual staircases, vaulted ceilings, and marble flooring. The gourmet kitchen includes high-end SS appliances and a large center island. All 4 bedrooms boast private en suites, with the primary suite spanning 1000 Sq Ft, featuring his and hers separate bathrooms and closets. The backyard oasis includes a covered patio, pool, and custom-built cabana. Additional highlights include a stunning theater with 150 inch screen, home office or 5th bedroom, private gym, custom den, and a four car garage. Elegant design, modern amenities, and a prime location make 14918 Lake Forest Dr an exceptional showcase.

Meta Title: 3720 Whitehall Drive Dallas, TX 75229 MLS#20485034
Meta Description: 3720 Whitehall Drive Dallas, TX 75229 $1,099,000 Situated on an expansive lot, this renovated ranch is close to top-tier private schools in North Dallas & zoned to Withers Elementary. Blt in speakers inside & out. Master suite has his-and-hers separate vanities, rain shower. Electric gate, oversized attached garage, new water heater, new HVAC. Lives larger than square footage!

Meta Title: Common Things to Look Out for Before Buying Your Dream Home
Meta Description: It is easy to become overwhelmed when you enter the home buying market. Friends, family, colleagues, and even acquaintances will give you their opinions if you are a first time home buyer. While most of them are looking out for your best interest, they are not fully aware of what is happening in the housing market.

Meta Title: Is Getting a Home Mortgage Still Too Difficult?
Meta Description: Potential homebuyers are always cautioned to be aware of mortgage lending standards and the difficulty they might face when trying to obtain a mortgage. Credit availability is expanding, making it easier to get a mortgage now than it was a year ago. The market is still tight however, and homebuyers should be prepared to shop around until they find a lender who is offering something that will meet the needs of their family.

Meta Title: Home Buying Wisdom: Assessing Affordability Beyond the Purchase Price
Meta Description: Discover the keys to smart home buying! Explore the financial essentials beyond the purchase price, from disciplined savings and comprehensive planning to maintaining a balanced Total Cost of Ownership. Ensure a secure and informed leap into homeownership with our expert insights.

Meta Title: Why You Should Consider Selling in the Winter
Meta Description: The season you sell your home can have an impact on how much you get for your home and how quickly it sells. The season that has the most success in selling homes is spring. This is a good time of year for families moving to new school districts and is also more convenient weather for moving. Because of this trend, most people will recommend waiting to list your home until after the winter is over. Avoiding the winter is a huge misconception in the housing industry and can cause homeowners to miss out on opportunities.

Meta Title: Will Increasing Mortgage Rates Impact Home Prices?
Meta Description: There has been some discussion recently on home prices in relation to mortgage rates. Some believe if there is a rapid rise of mortgage rates, home prices should decrease. Logically it makes the most sense for the price of the house to drop when interest rates are rising, but this is not always the case.

Meta Title: Senior Admissions Advisor
Meta Description: 3764 charactersInsides Salesperson / Senior Admissions AdvisorNew York, NY or remote About SERHANT. VenturesSERHANT. Ventures is building the #1 sales education platform for business professionals worldwide through our bestselling sales courses, membership, consulting, and coaching programs. These are currently under the brand name Sell It Like Serhant. Our mission is to empower our enrollees to achieve their limitless livelihood through mastery of sales.We’re on a rapid growth trajectory, realizing greater than 100% YOY revenue growth for the past three years with no outside investment while maintaining significant net profit margins. In addition to revenue success, we have enrolled over 10,000 students in 109 countries through our test market of real estate agents. Now, we’re expanding this year to the underserved, $15 billion market to train all salespeople worldwide, regardless of industry. About the RoleWe are seeking a driven salesperson to join our team as a Senior Admissions Advisor (Inside Sales Rep). You will be responsible for managing a high-volume sales pipeline to convert leads into students for our PRO consulting and coaching programs. This role will use a standardized sales process over phone and Zoom to guide prospective students through the enrollment process, matching their pain points to our solutions; helping them understand the value we provide in our relevant programs; overcoming objections; and ultimately enrolling students through their first payment and signed contract.This salesperson should expect to maintain a large sales pipeline and will need to be adept and comfortable with selling in large volume (one call close). We’re a self-starting, high-ownership, high-responsibility culture, and the right person will thrive on the independence afforded by this role. If you want unlimited growth potential and a culture where there is no “no” when it comes to generating creative sales ideas and new products, this is the role for you.ResponsibilitiesManage a large volume of prospective studentsMeet or exceed sales quotasOversee the entire admissions process, while offering consultation on potential program fitProspect potential students through previous inquiries and various outbound effortsOwn the entire navigation of the individual’s admissions journeyUse CRM software to track and measure all sales activityKnowledgeable about all SERHANT. Ventures products and able to direct individuals to the correct programOther duties as assigned About YouStrong Pipeline Management skillsStrong interpersonal skillsExcellent and timely follow-up 2-4 years of proven sales experience, ideally in consultative sales, admissions or recruitingExceptional closing skillsExperience exceeding a sales quotaAdaptable and able to function in a fast-paced, often-changing environmentWell organized and used to maintaining a large pipelinePassion for building client relationships and seeing opportunity around every cornerStrong obsession with relationship-based rather than transactional selling, because people hate being sold but they love shopping with friendsFamiliarity or expertise with HubSpot (or expertise with Salesforce and a willingness to learn HubSpot and incorporate best practices)Previous experience in Real Estate a plusPosition: Full-TimeSalary Range: $58,500 - $190,000No Cap on CommissionsWe provide equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender, gender identity or expression, age, national origin or ancestry, citizenship, disability, sexual orientation, marital status, pregnancy, veteran status, membership in the uniformed services, genetic information, or any other basis protected by applicable law.

Meta Title: Senior Creative Producer

This position is NYC based, with a hybrid work schedule, and reports to the Head of Content. Ability to coordinate large teams and keep them on schedule. Experience managing and running a production, including working with talent, efficiently and creatively Working knowledge of digital cinema cameras and lighting techniques; a sharp eye for what looks good on camera Strong collaborator with production and post-production teams, giving clear and actional feedback on things like editorial flow, edit rhythm, music, color, GFX, and sound Proven people management and coaching skills Flawless organizational skills, exceptional attention to detail and master of logistics. You foresee complications, make quick decisions, and troubleshoot on the fly Ability to learn, always improving yourself, and looking for innovative approaches How to Apply Please email Ankush Jindal, Head of Content, at ankush@serhant.com with your resume/portfolio, an explanation of why you’re interested, and what you can contribute to the team.
